# Feature Development Checklist

## Before Writing Any Code
- [ ] Verify feature aligns with ecommerce payment demo purpose
- [ ] Check if shadcn UI components can be used/extended
- [ ] Define TypeScript interfaces in `types/index.ts`
- [ ] Plan responsive design approach
- [ ] Consider accessibility requirements (ARIA, keyboard navigation)

## During Development
- [ ] Use `@/` imports for internal modules
- [ ] Import shadcn UI components from `@/components/ui/`
- [ ] Add proper TypeScript typing (no `any` types)
- [ ] Implement loading states for async operations
- [ ] Add error handling with user-friendly messages
- [ ] Include form validation where applicable
- [ ] Use semantic HTML elements
- [ ] Add ARIA labels and descriptions

## Code Quality Checks
- [ ] Run `pnpm lint` and fix all issues
- [ ] Ensure TypeScript compilation passes
- [ ] Test responsive design on mobile/tablet/desktop
- [ ] Verify keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Check color contrast for accessibility
- [ ] Test with screen reader (if possible)

## Integration Verification
- [ ] Component works with existing payment flow
- [ ] State management follows established patterns
- [ ] No breaking changes to existing functionality
- [ ] New types are properly exported
- [ ] Component is properly documented

## Before Committing
- [ ] All linting rules pass
- [ ] TypeScript compilation successful
- [ ] Component renders correctly across breakpoints
- [ ] No console errors or warnings
- [ ] Git commit follows conventional format
- [ ] Code follows established naming conventions

## Post-Development
- [ ] Update CLAUDE.md if architectural changes made
- [ ] Add component to appropriate documentation
- [ ] Consider adding to component library showcase
- [ ] Test deployment on Vercel (if applicable)

## Common Patterns to Follow
- Payment method selection components
- Form validation and error states
- Loading spinners and skeleton screens
- Responsive card layouts
- Accessible form inputs with labels
- Proper error boundaries
- Consistent spacing using Tailwind classes